> When it comes to comforting crowd-pleasers, any recipe with meatballs in it gets a thumbs up from us! As we're always looking for clever ways to cut down time in the kitchen, our beef suppliers have perfectly seasoned the meatballs so that you don't have to! Packing a serious flavour punch, and bursting with good-for-you ingredients, this spiced meatball stew is guaranteed to become your favourite quick-fix recipe.

== Rice ==

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch} for the rice.

When boiling add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{}, then return to the pan with the lid on, off the heat.

== Prep ==

Meanwhile, halve, then remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and thinly slice.

Halve the @cherry plum tomatoes{200%g}.

== Meatballs ==

Heat a splash of @oil{splash} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Add the @beef meatballs{240} and fry, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4%minutes}.

Add the pepper and stir-fry for another ~{2%minutes}.

== Stew ==

Stir in the cherry tomatoes, @rogan josh curry paste{17.5%g} and @curry garnish{15%g}, cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Pour in the @tomato passata{1}, @water{100%ml} and bring to the boil.

Reduce the heat and simmer until the meatballs are cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{6-7%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when they are no longer pink in the middle.

== Seasoning ==

Taste the stew and add a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} if needed.

== To Serve ==

Serve the rice in #bowls{} topped with the meatball stew.

Finish with a dollop of cooling @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Enjoy!